      <h3>Key Concept: The Equity Risk Premium (ERP)</h3>
      <p>Equity Risk Premium (ERP) is the extra return that investing in the stock market provides over a risk-free rate, such as a government bond. When JP Morgan issues a warning, they often highlight that the ERP is historically low. This simply means you are not getting paid enough extra return to justify the risk of buying stocks right now. Formula: ERP = Expected Market Return - Risk-Free Rate.</p>
